The paper discusses the use of attentional neural network layers for curiosity-based policies and exploration tasks, which are common topics in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). The exploration task also involves a 2D space, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
